The paper deals with algorithms for string matching, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The use of a dictionary and a stream of characters suggests that the paper may belong to the data structures (cs.DS) or discrete mathematics (cs.DM) categories. The algorithm's time and space complexity suggest that it may also belong to the computational complexity (cs.CC) or information theory (cs.IT) categories. Finally, the use of randomisation in the algorithm suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category.
